1. Input and print elements of an array

2. Find maximum element in array

3. Find minimum element

4. Find sum of array elements

5. Count even and odd numbers in array

6. Reverse the array

7. Copy one array to another

8. Sort array in ascending order

9. Merge two arrays

10. Remove duplicate elements

11. Write a program in Java that takes a size n from the user,
    then takes n characters as input to form a character array.
    Reverse the character array and print the reversed result
    as a string.